PARALYSIS (? TOXIC) - SCOTLAND (3)
==================================
Paralytic Shellfish Poisoning, and similar events, Scotland:
Cases are occasionally reported in Scotland and, more often, presence of
toxins from Dinoflagellates, in molluscs, is reported - and harvesting
of molluscs (and sometimes crustaceans) from affected areas is
temporarily banned.
These are generally noted in the SCIEH Weekly Report. Information might
be obtained from the:

Scottish Centre for Infection and Environmental Health,
Ruchill Hospital,
Glasgow, G20 9NB, Scotland.
telephone (UK) 0141-946-7120 Fax: 0141-946-4359.
--
David Stevenson
e-mail: ds@castle.ed.ac.uk
